At our school in the heart of The Bronx, we are dedicated to creating a vibrant, inclusive, and culturally responsive learning environment that celebrates and affirms the diverse identities of our students. Our mission is to empower every child to reach their fullest potential while fostering a strong sense of belonging and community.

We pride ourselves on our innovative bilingual dual language programs, which not only promote language acquisition but also honor our studentsâ cultural backgrounds. In addition to our academic offerings, we cultivate a deep appreciation for the arts. Our programming includes visual arts, music, dance, and drama, providing students with multiple avenues for creative expression. As a proud Save the Music school, we are committed to ensuring that every child has the opportunity to explore their musical talents, whether through playing the violin or participating in our comprehensive music curriculum.

To further enrich our studentsâ experiences, we offer cultural enrichment opportunities on Saturdays, where students can engage in activities ranging from coding to exploring various art forms. These programs are designed to ignite curiosity and foster lifelong learning.

We are honored to be a beacon of excellence in the Highbridge community, providing a safe haven for students navigating the complexities of an urban environment. Together, we are committed to nurturing well-rounded individuals who are prepared to make meaningful contributions to our world. We invite you to join our community and experience the transformative journey of learning with us. This school has a Bilingual Special Education (BSE) program: Open to students recommended for Bilingual Special Education (BSE) on their Individualized Education Plan (IEP). The Path Program provides support for students who have experienced trauma or stressful events, in an inclusive setting to learn in a district school alongside peers with and without IEPs. results.overview:
Our kindergarten program, both in our monolingual and dual language settings are designed to ensure that every student flourishes in their learning journey. Teaching and learning in kindergarten focuses on fostering a love for learning while supporting the development of social, emotional, cognitive, and physical skills. Activities are typically hands-on, which helps young children learn through exploration and experiences. Teachers facilitate learning by providing a variety of structured and unstructured activities that encourage curiosity, creativity, and foundational skills in literacy, numeracy and problem solving. We encourage children to take ownership of their learning by providing student choice and fostering a growth mindset. Developing social skills like sharing, taking turns, and empathy is also an essential part of our kindergarten curriculum as these skills are essential for future learning and personal growth. 

We have established learning centers where students rotate through different activities. These centers cover various subjects, including math, science, art, and literacy, allowing children to experiment and explore in a fun and engaging way.

Our program promotes collaboration through group projects and teamwork. By working together, students share ideas, solve problems, and learn from one another, fostering a strong sense of community within the classroom.
  
In our kindergarten program, students engage in a variety of specialty subjects. They participate in Physical Education (PE), music, dance, visual arts, and media. Within the media curriculum, students also explore coding and robotics, introducing them to important skills in technology. 
 This school has a Bilingual Special Education (BSE) program: Open to students recommended for Bilingual Special Education (BSE) on their Individualized Education Plan (IEP). If your child is recommended for BSE on their IEP and you have questions, visit www.schools.nyc.gov/specializedprograms or contact BSEprograms@schools.nyc.gov.
